1
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:16,733
Amanda!

2
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,533
You deserve it.

3
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:25,433
How dare you, Amanda!

4
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,200
Amanda, that's enough!

5
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:28,833
Thank you, Yenyen.

6
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:32,300
You made me happy
amid the uncertainty.

7
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,033
Thanks to you too.

8
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:38,000
You erase my fears and doubts.

9
00:00:38,067 --> 00:00:39,833
I feel more secure.

10
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:44,100
When we return to Manila, I will
introduce you to my parents.

11
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,867
I will also introduce
you to my mom.

12
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:48,533
I will tell her
that a kindhearted

13
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,800
and good-looking prince charming
took care of me on this island.

14
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:54,700
Rina, you're hurting
other people too.

15
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,700
Why? Wait a minute, Victor.

16
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:57,700
Are they the only
ones who got hurt?

17
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,433
Was I not hurt?

18
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,667
She deserves to suffer!

19
00:01:01,733 --> 00:01:03,600
Red needs us.

20
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,733
Stop living in the past.

21
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,300
Red and I are
going home, coach.

22
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:11,167
I will remember
everything you taught me.

23
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:14,567
Every moment you've
shared with me.

24
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:17,767
And coach, I'd also like
to ask for your blessing

25
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,400
for our relationship.

26
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:23,600
I promise I will
never make her cry.

27
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:27,067
Haunt me if I do that.

28
00:01:30,767 --> 00:01:33,633
It might already be
dark when we get there.

29
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:34,667
It's okay.

30
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:37,600
I only hope for smooth sailing.

31
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:40,167
Let's pray that we see
a fisherman.

32
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:42,167
Or an inhabited island.

33
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:44,067
We'll ask them for help.

34
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:45,500
Red, I'm scared.

35
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,967
We can do this.

36
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,867
Don't be scared.

37
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,400
Go on, get in.

38
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:02,300
Let's go.

39
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:28,733
Red, get some rest for now.

40
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:55,200
How long do you think it
will take us to find help?

41
00:02:57,167 --> 00:03:01,267
Who knows? We might see
a fisherman soon.

42
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:05,067
Or an inhabited island
where we can find help.

43
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:08,033
I got my flashlight ready.

44
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,900
I got my whistle too.

45
00:03:12,867 --> 00:03:15,333
Let's stay positive, okay?

46
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,467
Red?

47
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,667
What's the first thing you will
do when we get back to Manila?

48
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:45,167
I will hug my parents.

49
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:49,400
And then I will
introduce them to you.

50
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:55,567
And we will be together...

51
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:56,800
forever.

52
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:23,867
I will hug my mom too.

53
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:28,300
And I will kiss
her over and over.

54
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:34,767
I will make up for the moments
I didn't get to kiss her.

55
00:04:36,733 --> 00:04:38,767
Then, I will go back to school.

56
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,100
Because I want to be a lawyer.

57
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:48,733
I want to help the poor people
who don't get justice

58
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,133
like my mom.

59
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,433
Did your mom go to jail
even if she's innocent?

60
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,567
What was her case?

61
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:04,200
And who sent her to jail?

62
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:23,200
Hey, girls.

63
00:05:23,267 --> 00:05:24,600
Have you eaten yet?

64
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,133
You haven't eaten yet?

65
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,700
Wait here. I'll be right back.

66
00:05:28,767 --> 00:05:30,733
I have some rice cakes
that I didn't get to sell.

67
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,733
Wait.

68
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,867
Here.

69
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:53,000
- There you go.
- Thank you.

70
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:55,000
Thank you!

71
00:05:55,067 --> 00:05:56,300
Go ahead.

72
00:06:02,233 --> 00:06:04,900
Wherever my daughter is,

73
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:11,433
I hope someone is giving her
food to satisfy her hunger.

74
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:23,867
I think something is off.

75
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:27,067
The sea looks calm.

76
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:29,833
But we're moving fast.

77
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:34,367
Red, there's an undertow!

78
00:06:43,567 --> 00:06:44,300
Yen...

79
00:06:44,367 --> 00:06:45,400
Yen, hold on tight.

80
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:49,400
Red, row in the other direction!

81
00:06:49,467 --> 00:06:50,667
Yen!

82
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:51,800
Yen, there are rocks!

83
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:52,633
Hold on tight!

84
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:53,933
Tie yourself up!

85
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,700
We're going to hit the rocks!

86
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:56,800
Hold on tight!

87
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:30,167
Yen!

88
00:07:33,533 --> 00:07:34,767
Red!

89
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:56,533
Hello?

90
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,600
Sir Victor,

91
00:07:57,667 --> 00:08:00,533
they recovered remains
from the plane crash.

92
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,567
They were students
at your son's school.

93
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:03,867
Is it Red?

94
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:05,167
My son?

95
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,633
Thank goodness.

96
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:13,267
I got my capital back
and a little profit.

97
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,933
This is for you, Eden.

98
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,367
Hello?

99
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:42,800
Ma'am Amanda, some passengers'
remains were recovered.

100
00:08:42,867 --> 00:08:44,933
Your daughter might
be one of them.

101
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,267
My god.

102
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,433
Please, not my daughter.

103
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:01,133
Hello, Dindi?

104
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,367
Are you there yet?

105
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:04,800
I'm already at the morgue.

106
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:06,700
I'm sorry,

107
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:10,367
I'm still here at the office
where I'm applying for a job.

108
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:12,733
I'll go there once
I finish here.

109
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:17,100
I feel...

110
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:24,333
I feel like...

111
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,733
I feel like my
knees are shaking.

112
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,067
I'm feeling weak.

113
00:09:32,767 --> 00:09:36,633
I feel that Yenyen
is still alive but...

114
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:43,700
I'm scared to go
and check the remains.

115
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:48,600
What if Yenyen is one of them?

116
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:52,100
You have to be strong, Amanda.

117
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,867
It's out of our control.

118
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,933
We only have God's mercy.

119
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:11,467
We can't do anything if he
wants to take Yenyen from us.

120
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:19,500
But if he still wants
us to be together,

121
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:21,367
he will make it happen.

122
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:25,200
Amanda?

123
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:33,767
I'm already by the door.

124
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,967
I'll call you
again later, okay?

125
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:53,033
God, I lift up
everything to you.

126
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:58,300
It's hard to accept it but,

127
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:05,167
may your will...

128
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,233
be done.

129
00:11:27,533 --> 00:11:29,467
Are you sure you
can't wait for me?

130
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:31,333
The traffic is a bit bad.

131
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,467
No.

132
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:34,200
Just follow me there.

133
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:37,100
I want to see the remains
as soon as possible.

134
00:11:37,167 --> 00:11:39,967
I want to know if
Red is one of them.

135
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,500
You might not be
able to handle it.

136
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,600
Victor, please!

137
00:11:43,667 --> 00:11:45,833
I cannot wait any longer.

138
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:52,367
I've been wanting to know
what happened to our child.

139
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:54,267
I don't want to
prolong our agony.

140
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:59,200
I want to find out if our
son is already dead or not.

141
00:11:59,267 --> 00:11:59,867
Okay, okay.

142
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,100
Calm down.

143
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:03,700
Let's meet there.

144
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,167
Are you okay, Rina?

145
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,367
What kind of question is that?

146
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:16,167
I once lost a child.

147
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,600
I don't want it to happen again.

148
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,933
I don't think we should go.

149
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,700
You shouldn't look at it.

150
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:24,700
And then what?

151
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,700
Live in fantasy?

152
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:31,667
I'm tired of hoping.

153
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:34,567
I want to know.

154
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:38,700
I want to know if my son
is already dead or still alive.

155
00:12:38,767 --> 00:12:40,833
I want to know...

156
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:44,633
if I should keep waiting.

157
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,233
Yes, Ma'am?

158
00:12:58,833 --> 00:12:59,967
Sir,

159
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:06,533
can I look at the bodies...

160
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,733
that were recovered
from the plane crash?

161
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,567
There are still two
unidentified bodies.

162
00:13:13,633 --> 00:13:15,700
One male and one female.

163
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:17,333
They were found
at the same time.

164
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,667
I want to see the female.

165
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:27,867
Here it is.

166
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:38,767
Do you want me to help you?

167
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,133
I can do it.

168
00:14:11,533 --> 00:14:13,233
She's not my daughter.

169
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,567
She's not my daughter.

170
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:17,300
Thank you.

171
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,400
Where is he?

172
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:51,800
Where's the body you recovered
from the plane crash?

173
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:53,133
What is his name?

174
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,500
There's still one male body
that hasn't been identified yet.

175
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:56,667
Here he is, Ma'am.

176
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:22,933
He's not my son.

177
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,233
He's not my child.

178
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:31,367
He's not my son.

179
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,333
Victor!

180
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,333
Yes, Rina?

181
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,300
Rina, is it Red?

182
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:50,967
It's not our son!

183
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:53,133
It's not Red.

184
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,233
It's not him.

185
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,900
I almost fainted.

186
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:02,967
I don't know what
to do if it's Red.

187
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:05,800
It's not our son, Victor.

188
00:16:05,867 --> 00:16:07,667
Thank God!

189
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:13,200
Well, at least for now, we can
still hope that Red is alive.

190
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,700
But for how long, Victor?

191
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:17,833
How long should we hope?

192
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:26,900
Hello, Dindi?

193
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:31,933
Yenyen is...

194
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,900
Yenyen is not dead.

195
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:38,567
Thank God.

196
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:41,967
I'm so worried for you.

197
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:45,900
I can feel her even
if I'm away from her.

198
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:48,800
I feel that she's still alive.

199
00:16:48,867 --> 00:16:50,867
Mothers are like that.

200
00:16:50,933 --> 00:16:54,533
They can feel what's
happening to their children.

201
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,533
Don't worry.

202
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:59,800
We'll keep on praying
for Yenyen.

203
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:01,633
We will see her soon.

204
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:04,767
I believe in the
power of prayer.

205
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:12,967
Red...

206
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:14,867
Red!

207
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,667
Red!

208
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:18,700
Where are you?

209
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:21,233
Where are you, Red?

210
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,867
Red.

211
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:29,100
Miss?

212
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,500
Miss?

213
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,067
Miss?

214
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:37,933
Oh my god.

215
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,433
Miss?

216
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:45,433
Miss!

217
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:46,600
You're alive!

218
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,367
Come on.

219
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:50,100
Wait...

220
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:51,167
Where...

221
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:53,133
Where...

222
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:55,667
Oh my God!

223
00:17:57,667 --> 00:17:58,633
Miss!

224
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:15,433
Mr. Flores.

225
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:16,767
No, no, no.

226
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:18,033
Mr. Flores, no.

227
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:21,567
The moment you borrow money,
there's already an interest.

228
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:22,600
Yes.

229
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:25,767
It doesn't matter
if you pay the day after.

230
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:28,267
We had it in our agreement.

231
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,867
Oh, wow.

232
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,767
You're here too.

233
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:37,967
So?

234
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,100
Should I order a coffin for you?

235
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,100
My daughter's not dead.

236
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,500
Oh, really?

237
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:47,567
Too bad.

238
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:49,700
I wish it was your
daughter who died.

239
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:52,133
Why not die instead?

240
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,400
Oh, sorry.

241
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:56,967
Bad people live longer.

242
00:18:57,067 --> 00:19:00,600
If there's someone bad
in here, that's you.

243
00:19:00,667 --> 00:19:03,433
And I won't be surprised
if you lose a child

244
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:06,133
because that's karma.

245
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:09,567
You killed my son, so your
daughter should die this time.

246
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:11,067
That will never happen.

247
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,900
Why not?

248
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:15,833
I'll take care of her coffin.

249
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:17,167
I know a place that offers two
coffins for the price of one.

250
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,233
You can have the other coffin.

251
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:23,233
Your mouth really is filthy.

252
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:27,267
It won't get clean even if I use
three gallons of alcohol on you.

253
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,367
Can you afford
three gallons?

254
00:19:29,467 --> 00:19:31,800
You can't even afford 30 ml.

255
00:19:31,867 --> 00:19:34,167
And you have the guts to
talk about three gallons.

256
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:36,800
Why don't you just go
back to your province?

257
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:39,367
Many are waiting for you there.

258
00:19:39,433 --> 00:19:42,233
What province are
you talking about?

259
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:45,033
Hell. You're from there, right?

260
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,367
Maybe you're the one
who came from hell.

261
00:19:48,433 --> 00:19:50,467
You know why?
Because you're a murderer!

262
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:52,800
Your horns are already showing.

263
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:53,733
And your tail too!

264
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,267
You're turning into a demon!

265
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,967
How dare you!

266
00:19:58,033 --> 00:19:59,300
You witch!

267
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,967
You're a beast!

268
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,967
You!

269
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,967
Oh my God.

270
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:56,367
Wait. You should
have rested more.

271
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:57,467
Come here.

272
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:58,333
Are you okay?

273
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,967
You might get dizzy again.

274
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:01,100
Sit down first.

275
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,200
Oh my God. You hurt your head.

276
00:21:06,267 --> 00:21:07,700
Drink this.

277
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,567
Hello.

278
00:21:10,633 --> 00:21:11,633
I'm Sabina.

279
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,300
What's your name?

280
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,567
I'm Yenyen.

281
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:17,900
I'm okay.

282
00:21:17,967 --> 00:21:20,300
My head just hurts a little.

283
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:26,500
Wait.

284
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:31,167
Where did you get
your jungle bolo?

285
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:35,300
I just found a suitcase
with a jungle bolo.

286
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:41,100
I also found a tent with
a lot of supplies we can use.

287
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:44,600
That's the only thing I
saw from the plane crash.

288
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:47,333
I thought I was
the only survivor.

289
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,800
And then, thank God I found you.

290
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:56,067
Wait, so that means you're
also stranded on this island?

291
00:21:56,133 --> 00:21:56,800
Yes.

292
00:21:56,867 --> 00:21:59,433
I've been alone here.

293
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,667
You don't know how much
I've been looking

294
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:02,900
for other survivors.

295
00:22:10,533 --> 00:22:12,733
Wait, why are you crying?

296
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:18,367
We were on the other island.

297
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:21,300
We stayed there
for several days.

298
00:22:21,367 --> 00:22:28,900
Then we took the courage
to sail to find help.

299
00:22:28,967 --> 00:22:30,367
But...

300
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:34,333
Don't cry.

301
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,300
What matters is you're alive.

302
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:41,867
But you said you
were with someone.

303
00:22:41,933 --> 00:22:43,767
Yes.

304
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:46,500
How many people
did you sail with?

305
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:49,033
We were two.

306
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:50,467
Do you know where he is?

307
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:51,900
I don't know.

308
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:57,267
We got separated when
the raft collapsed.

309
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:59,733
I hope he's okay.

310
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,100
I hope he's safe.

311
00:23:02,167 --> 00:23:03,067
Sorry.

312
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:06,033
Sorry for being emotional.

313
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:08,867
That person is special to me.

314
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:15,733
We made a promise that
we would be together.

315
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,867
He made a promise.

316
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:20,700
He promised me that we
would never get separated.

317
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:23,567
Yen!

318
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:29,500
Yenyen!

319
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:33,267
Yenyen, where are you?

320
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:38,033
Yen, where are you?

321
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:46,167
Yen!

322
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:48,967
Yen, I can't lose you!

323
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,500
Sorry.

324
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:56,733
I'm sorry for being emotional.

325
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:58,900
He's special to me.

326
00:23:58,967 --> 00:24:01,333
That person is dear to me.

327
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:08,433
We became a couple
on the island.

328
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:11,467
We got very close.

329
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:15,567
It's okay.

330
00:24:15,633 --> 00:24:18,333
Actually, I understand.

331
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:25,267
Because my boyfriend is
so special to me too.

332
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,400
So...

333
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,667
I was so sad too

334
00:24:29,767 --> 00:24:31,367
when we got separated.

335
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,300
We feel the same.

336
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:38,833
I hope we find them.

337
00:24:39,967 --> 00:24:42,433
I miss Red.

338
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:49,200
Red?

339
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:50,567
Yes.

340
00:24:50,633 --> 00:24:53,600
Red is the name of the man
I was with on the island.

341
00:24:59,967 --> 00:25:01,400
Yen!

342
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,267
Yen, where are you?

343
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:04,100
Put your hands in the air!

344
00:25:04,167 --> 00:25:05,133
Who are you?

345
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,967
How did you know Yen?

346
00:25:07,033 --> 00:25:09,300
OMG!

347
00:25:09,367 --> 00:25:11,200
Red, is that you?

348
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:12,533
Wait, Rina.

349
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,867
Are we going to leave
Amanda like that?

350
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:16,000
Amanda's here?

351
00:25:16,067 --> 00:25:17,367
Help!

352
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:18,633
I need to move.

353
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:20,000
I need to find Red.

354
00:25:20,067 --> 00:25:20,800
Red?

355
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:22,533
Red?

356
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:23,733
Oh my God!
